    dc:creator "Tominaga, Atsushi; Matsui, Masafumi; Nishikawa, Kanto" ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "Two new species of lotic breeding salamanders (Amphibia, Caudata, Hynobiidae) from western Japan" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625633>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625635>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625637>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625641>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625627> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625633>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Dorsal and ventral views of male holotype (KUHE 30218) of Hynobius sematonotos n. sp. A, B), male holotype (KUHE 27267) of Hynobius oyamai n. sp. (C, D), and supposed topotypic male specimen (KUHE 28637) of H. naevius from Tara-cho, Saga Prefecture. Scale bar shows 50 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625633/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625635>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. vomerine teeth series of male holotype (KUHE 30218) of Hynobius sematonotos n. sp. (A), male holotype (KUHE 27267) of Hynobius oyamai n. sp. (B), and supposed topotypic male specimen (KUHE 28637) of H. naevius (C) from Taracho, Saga Prefecture. Scale bar indicates 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625635/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625637>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Egg sacs of Hynobius sematonotos n. sp. from Shobara-shi, Hiroshima Prefecture (A) and egg sacs of Hynobius oyamai n. sp. from Yamaga-shi, Kumamoto Prefecture (B). Scale bar in (B) shows 5 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625637/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625641>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views of a full-grown larva (Stage 62) of Hynobius sematonotos n. sp. from Higashihiroshima-shi, Hiroshima Prefecture (type locality). Dorsal (C), lateral (D), and ventral (E) views of a full-grown larva (Stage 63) of Hynobius oyamai n. sp. from Kitakyushu-shi, Fukuoka Prefecture (type locality). Scale bar shows 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625641/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625627>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map of western Japan and distributional range of Hynobius naevius and two new species. Range filled by oblique lines: distributional range of H. naevius; range filled by horizontal line: distributional range of H. sematonotos n. sp.; range filled by vertical lines: distributional range of H. oyamai n. sp. Closed symbols: sampling locality used in this study. Closed triangle: supposed type locality and sampling locality of topotypic specimens of H. naevius. Closed star: type locality of H. sematonotos n. sp. Closed diamond: type locality of H. oyamai n. sp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625627/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

